g.title: Zbigniew Brzezinski
g.text: Zbigniew Brzezinski

g.text: Critic of Putin's leadership

g.text: Zdravka Bušić

g.title: Zdravka Bušić->Vladimir Putin
g.text: Signed cooperation agreement in his presence

g.title: Ze'ev Elkin
g.text: Ze'ev Elkin

g.text: Interpreter for meetings with

g.title: Zechariah Baumel
g.text: Zechariah Baumel

• Served as a tank commander in the Israel Defense Forces during the 1982 Lebanon War.

g.text: Remains recovered with assistance from

g.text: Zelimkhan Khangoshvili

g.title: Zelimkhan Khangoshvili->Vladimir Putin
g.text: Accused by of orchestrating assassination

g.text: Represented by attorney from Putin's friend's law firm

g.title: Zhang Deguang
g.text: Zhang Deguang

g.text: Awarded Commemorative Medal by Vladimir Putin in March 2004

g.title: Zhang Guoqing

g.text: Met with Vladimir Putin at the Eastern Economic Forum in 2023

g.text: Zhores Alferov

g.title: Zhores Alferov->Vladimir Putin
g.text: Signer of an open letter to against clericalisation

g.text: Zhou Libo (comedian)

g.text: Criticized Vladimir Putin in a Weibo post

g.title: Zinaida Korneva
g.text: Zinaida Korneva
• Launched a charity initiative in April 2020 to support Russian doctors during the COVID-19 pandemic, raising 4.5 million rubles.

g.title: Zinaida Korneva->Vladimir Putin

g.text: Ziyavudin Magomedov
• In March 2018, he was arrested in Russia on charges of embezzlement and sentenced to 19 years in prison, later reduced to 18.5 years.

g.title: Ziyavudin Magomedov->Vladimir Putin

g.title: Zoran Milanović

g.title: Zori Balayan
g.text: Zori Balayan

g.title: Ólafur Ragnar Grímsson->Vladimir Putin
g.text: Met during a state visit to Russia

g.text: Čedomir Stojković

g.title: Čedomir Stojković->Vladimir Putin
g.text: Opposes regime influence in Serbia

g.text: İlber Ortaylı

g.text: Apologist for Vladimir Putin's regime

g.text: Šefik Džaferović
